7.3. Work Order Printout

  


Requirements

Purpose/Overview: This is a basic, production-facing (internal) PDF of the materials (i.e. individual Items) for "Awarded" Groups (and their linked Sections) in a Proposal. This can be generated for an entire Proposal or for a selection of one or more Groups. 

  


Printed From: 

  * "Work Order PDF (Complete)" link on the Proposal record (see corresponding spec)
  * "Work Order PDF (Partial)" link on the Proposal record (see corresponding spec)



  


File Format/Name: PDF:

  * If "Job Type" = "Residential": "Work Order <Proposal #> \- <Customer Last Name>, <Customer First Name> (<Customer Primary Address Line 1>; <Job Type>)"
    * Example: "Work Order 15001 - Byler, John (1234 Some St; Residential)"
  * If "Job Type" = any other: "Work Order <Proposal #> \- <Customer Name> (<Job Name>; <Job Type>)"
    * Example: "Work Order 15002 - ABC Builders (Ephrata Community Park; Commercial)" 



  


Fields to be Filled: 

  


  * Proposal # (displays the "Proposal #")



  


  * "Customer Details" section:
    * Name (displays the name of the Customer, with the following details / behaviors:
      * for Organizations: displays the "Name" from the Contact record (not the Display Name);
      * for Individuals: displays the name from the Contact record in the "FirstName LastName" format (not the Display Name) 
    * Address (displays the "Customer Address", in the standard multi-line format without the addressee name) 
    * Phone (displays the "Customer Phone") 
    * Email (displays the "Customer Email") 



  


  * "Job Details" section:
    * Sales Rep (displays the name of the Sales Rep, in the "FirstName LastName" format)
    * Job Type (displays the "Job Type")
    * Job Name (displays the "Job Name")
    * Address (displays the "Job Address", in the standard multi-line format without the addressee name)



  


  * "Job Contact Details" section:
    * Name (displays the "Job Contact"t)
    * Phone (displays the "Job Contact Phone")
    * Email (displays the "Job Contact Email")



  


  * "Work Order Itemization" section:
    * Table with the following: 
      * Rows:
        * Includes a simple row for each included Section. This that starts above the "Item" column and has a "Section:" prefix, followed by the Section details, which are displayed in the same format as on the Proposal Printout (see spec for "Section" column there).
        * Includes a "heading" row for each Group. This that starts above the "Item" column, below the "Section:" row as applicable, and has a "Group:" prefix, followed by the "Group Description". This row has a dark yellow background (RGB: 243, 185, 44).; 
        * Includes a row for each Item under its corresponding Group (see details in the "Item" column spec below). 
      * Columns: 
        * Item (allows for text wrapping, if the displayed text is longer than the width of the column; displays the "Item Description") 
        * Item Price (displays the "Group Printout Price $" for the Item; note that this is not the Unit Price) 
        * Qty (displays the "Item Qty" for the Item) 



  


Handling Page Breaks: This printout sometimes extends beyond a single page; in those cases, the following guidelines are considered:

Can split between any rows, but do not split a row (i.e. if the text is long enough to wrap to multiple lines)

  


Other Notes:

  * Includes page numbers at the bottom of the page, in the "Page __ of __" format.
  * Includes the default "Powered by Silverloom Business Suite" footnote at the bottom of the page.
  * Noted that Leacock had requested to have the column headings repeated on each page, but this is not reasonably possible at the time of Phase 1, with the current capabilities of the PDF templating tools. 
  * Note that printout templates may be subject to limitations of the PDF templating library. CCI will communicate with the client in places where the template library requires significant changes from the original design.
